full_text:
Not that many people responded to the 1st call for participants, even though it was paid.

Getting photographers to commit to a date was much, much harder than I thought.

The theme seemed to be that people weren't taking me or this project seriously.
full_text(utf-8):
b"Not that many people responded to the 1st call for participants, even though it was paid.

Getting photographers to commit to a date was much, much harder than I thought.

The theme seemed to be that people weren't taking me or this project seriously."

full_text: But! A friend reminded me that if I really wanted to do it, I'd find a way. So I realized that I could scale back and doing something small was better than not doing it at all. I sucked up my pride, emailed orgs and people, and scraped together $2000 for the first shoot.
full_text(utf-8): b"But! A friend reminded me that if I really wanted to do it, I'd find a way. So I realized that I could scale back and doing something small was better than not doing it at all. I sucked up my pride, emailed orgs and people, and scraped together $2000 for the first shoot."

full_text: Sometimes I get really caught up in doing the work and I forget to stop and take a second to take it all in. At the beginning of this year, #DisabledAndHere was a few photos from a test shoot and a failed Kickstarter.

full_text:
@vicster Unfortunately, I have even worse stories of toxic tech environments. And sexism.

I somehow didn‚Äôt put together how many abusive people I‚Äôve had to work for until today?
full_text(utf-8): b'@vicster Unfortunately, I have even worse stories of toxic tech environments. And sexism.\n\nI somehow didn\xe2\x80\x99t put together how many abusive people I\xe2\x80\x99ve had to work for until today?'

full_text:
Eventually I managed to find another startup who was willing to do transfer paperwork for my work visa.

The first startup did not take this well & made sure my last weeks were miserable.

For years after, I hid my disability & continued to overwork before finally quitting tech.
full_text(utf-8):
b'Eventually I managed to find another startup who was willing to do transfer paperwork for my work visa.

The first startup did not take this well & made sure my last weeks were miserable.

For years after, I hid my disability & continued to overwork before finally quitting tech.'

full_text:
One day the HR manager pulled me aside and accused me of faking health issues and taking advantage of the startup. She thought I was ‚Äúscamming‚Äù them for work sponsorship.

I started crying in the office and knew I needed to leave.
full_text(utf-8): b'One day the HR manager pulled me aside and accused me of faking health issues and taking advantage of the startup. She thought I was \xe2\x80\x9cscamming\xe2\x80\x9d them for work sponsorship.\n\nI started crying in the office and knew I needed to leave.'

full_text:
The startup actually did have an HR manager. Though she was far from a professional. She was close friends with my manager and I started noticing higher ups all being colder and more dismissive to me.

I started hiding in the bathroom for breaks.
full_text(utf-8): b'The startup actually did have an HR manager. Though she was far from a professional. She was close friends with my manager and I started noticing higher ups all being colder and more dismissive to me.\n\nI started hiding in the bathroom for breaks.'

full_text:
So I went to other teams directly and asked them how I could help. The content and blog folks loved me.

My manager continued to be either passive aggressive or outright hostile and boxed me further out of actual product design work.
full_text(utf-8): b'So I went to other teams directly and asked them how I could help. The content and blog folks loved me.\n\nMy manager continued to be either passive aggressive or outright hostile and boxed me further out of actual product design work.'

full_text:
I asked my manager if I could take on more tasks, since my work responsibilities every Agile sprint regularly equaled only 2-3 days of work for me.

He refused and said the work I was completing wasn‚Äôt good anyway, but refused to elaborate on why or what I could improve on.
full_text(utf-8): b'I asked my manager if I could take on more tasks, since my work responsibilities every Agile sprint regularly equaled only 2-3 days of work for me.\n\nHe refused and said the work I was completing wasn\xe2\x80\x99t good anyway, but refused to elaborate on why or what I could improve on.'

full_text:
When I returned to work, I still didn‚Äôt have a diagnosis and obviously wasn‚Äôt ‚Äúall better.‚Äù

But I wanted to prove myself and I always stayed after hours and completed all the tasks assigned to me done early.
full_text(utf-8): b'When I returned to work, I still didn\xe2\x80\x99t have a diagnosis and obviously wasn\xe2\x80\x99t \xe2\x80\x9call better.\xe2\x80\x9d\n\nBut I wanted to prove myself and I always stayed after hours and completed all the tasks assigned to me done early.'

full_text:
My company started to get suspicious.

Awhile later, I had to take extended (again, unpaid) time off. Because my body wasn‚Äôt cooperating and I just could not make the hour+ commute to get to work.
full_text(utf-8): b'My company started to get suspicious.\n\nAwhile later, I had to take extended (again, unpaid) time off. Because my body wasn\xe2\x80\x99t cooperating and I just could not make the hour+ commute to get to work.'

full_text: During my hospital stay, my company apparently called the hospital repeatedly to find out where I was. They refused to give any info, because HIPAA.
full_text(utf-8): b'During my hospital stay, my company apparently called the hospital repeatedly to find out where I was. They refused to give any info, because HIPAA.'

full_text: I was still in the early stages of my disability manifesting and trying to get a diagnosis and my neurologist suggested a week-long hospital stay. I requested it well in advance and it was granted, unpaid.

full_text: Whoops, I should've put "fine" in quotes in that earlier tweet. Because being disabled doesn't make me not fine, except in minds of other people. People just keep pushing back when I'm trying to find ways to not only exist but be my full self in a space.

full_text: It‚Äôs been illuminating  going back and forth between visible and invisible disability. I‚Äôve been disabled for over 10 years and I guess people just assume since I don‚Äôt talk about it all the time, I‚Äôve been fine.
